					<head>Liturgy</head>
					<msContents class="lccn.loc.gov/n80040114" rend="visible">
						<summary>A daily prayer book according to the rite used in Corfu.</summary>
						<textLang mainLang="he"/>
						<msItem n="0" rend="visible" class="lccn.loc.gov/n80040114">
							<locus from="1r" to="178v"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Maḥzor</title>
							<title xml:lang="he">מחזור</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="3r" to="30r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Morning prayers</title>
							<note>
								<p>The order begins with the song of Hannah (1Sam. 2), followed by other verses from Scripture.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="30r" to="35r"/>
							<title xml:lang="he-Latn-x-lc">Piyuṭim</title>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="35r" to="66v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Prayers for special Sabbaths</title>
							<note>
								<p>Seder Shabat ṿe-rosh ḥodesh begins on folio 35r; Seder Shabat ṿe-Ḥanukah - folio 38r; Seder Shabat sheḳalim - folio 42r; Seder Shabat zekhor - folio 46r; Seder Shabat parah - folio 53r; Seder Shabat ha-ḥodesh - folio 57r; Seder Shabat ha-gadol shel Pesaḥ - folio 60r.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="66v" to="122v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Pesaḥ</title>
							<note>
								<p>Seder ῾arvit shel Pesaḥ begins on folio 66v; Seder yom rishon shel Pesaḥ - folio 83r; Seder yom sheni shel Pesaḥ - folio 92r; Seder Shabat ṿe-ḥol ha-mo῾ed shel Pesaḥ - folio 98r; Seder lel shevi῾i shel Pesaḥ - folio 107r; Seder yom shemini shel Pesaḥ - folio 115r.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="122v" to="142r"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Shavu῾ot</title>
							<note>
								<p>Seder Shabat gadol shel Shavu῾ot begins on folio 122v; ῾Arvit le-Shavu῾ot - folio 127r; Seder yom rishon shel Shavu῾ot - folio 128r; Seder yom sheni shel Shavu῾ot - folio 138r.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
						<msItem rend="">
							<locus from="142r" to="178v"/>
							<title xml:lang="en">Services for Sukot</title>
							<note>
								<p>῾Arvit for Sukot begins on folio 142r; Seder yom rishon shel Sukot - folio 143r; Seder yom sheni shel Sukot - folio 149r; Seder Shabat ṿe-ḥol ham-mo῾ed shel Sukot - folio 152r; ῾Arvit le-Shemini ῾atseret - folio 157v; Seder yom Shemini ῾atseret - folio 158r; Seder lel Simḥah Torah - folio 163v; Seder yom Simḥah Torah - folio 163v. Appended is Israel Nagara's Ketuvah le-shavu῾ot.</p>
							</note>
						</msItem>
					</msContents>
